    "moralLesson": "This text establishes the theological foundation of patience: divine companionship. The Quranic promise 'Allah is with the patient' (2:153, 8:46) transforms patience from mere endurance into a means of experiencing Allah's special presence. Patience (sabr) is not passive resignation but active trust that invites divine help. The cause-effect relationship is clear: difficulty comes → you practice patience → Allah loves you → Allah helps you → you become close to Allah. This progression shows patience as a transformative spiritual practice, not just a coping mechanism. The imperative verbs (اصْبِرُوا، اصْبِرْ) make patience an active command, not optional advice.",
